The Cabinet for Health and Family Services shall prepare the following reports to the General Assembly on child-care programs, and shall make them available to the public:
A quarterly report detailing the number of children and amounts of child-care subsidies provided in each area development district;
A quarterly report on administrative expenses incurred in the operation of child-care subsidy programs;
A quarterly report on disbursements of federal child-care block grant funds for training, resource and referral, and similar activities; and
Beginning July 15, 1993, an annual report summarizing the average child-care subsidy activities per month in all Kentucky counties.
